Qatar Will Set Up 1,400 Farms on 45,000 Hectares, Peninsula Says

-- B y   R o b e r t   T u t t l e
-- 
2011-08-02T06:58:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/qatar-will-set-up-1-400-farms-on-45-000-hectares-peninsula-says.html
Qatar plans to set up 1,400 farms
covering 45,000 hectares (111,200 acres) of land, to achieve
self-sufficiency in food production,  The Peninsula  reported,
citing Fahd bin Mohamed Al Attiyah, the chairman of the Qatar
National Food Security Program.  Qatar has 65,000 hectares of arable land, the newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Tuttle in Doha at 
 rtuttle@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss on   sev@bloomberg.net  